&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Informatics Training &amp; Support Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A position has arisen within the Informatics Training and Support Team for a Senior Informatics Training &amp; Support Officer. This is an exciting time for the Trust while we implement a new PAS at all our sites this is an opportunity to be part of a team to offer support and training to our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior member of the team, you will be responsible for supporting the Trust’s applications on a daily basis. You will be expected to help on the implementation and operation of all aspects of the Trust’s Clinical and Business applications. You will also be required to train our colleagues in the use of the supported applications. The role is varied and you will be involved with our existing PAS systems across all sites and the PAS Project Team in the implementation of the new Medway PAS and other systems new to North West Anglia Foundation Trust. The role is varied and challenging, other responsibilities include supervising the team and scheduling the department training and support diary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While the role may be based at either of our main sites at Peterborough or Huntingdon cross site working will be required. Additionally, we offer both onsite and remote working opportunities. We are looking for someone who has knowledge of our current systems along with excellent communication skills and a willingness to learn new systems. Ideally you will have experience of a training role and should have an understanding of projects, knowledge of the NHS and clinical systems would be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLynn LucasJob titleClinical Systems ManagerEmail addresslynnlucas1@nhs.netTelephone number01480 428978Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amy Riley - amy.riley@nhs.net or Lee Dransfield - lee.dransfield@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
